==Old English==
===Etymology===
Cognate with Old Frisian [[krenza]], Old Saxon [[krengen]] ‘heel over’.

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'kɹɪnʤan/

===Verb===
'''crincgan''' (class III strong: '''crincgeþ''' ‘he falls’, '''cranc''' ‘he fell’, '''cruncon''' ‘they fell’, '''ġecruncen''' ‘fallen’)
# to [[fall]], [[yield]]
# to fall or die in battle

